ocaml-sdl
------------------------------------------
The goal of OCamlSDL is to provide access the multimedia hardware
in the ML programming language with the help of the SDL library.
The Simple DirectMedia Layer is a generic API that provides low
level access to audio, keyboard, mouse, and display framebuffer across
multiple platforms.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.7-1
  libSDL1.2_0-1.2.14-1
  libSDL_gfx13-2.0.20-1
  libSDL_image1.2_0-1.2.10-2
  libSDL_mixer1.2_0-1.2.11-1
  libSDL_ttf2.0_0-2.0.9-10
  ocaml-base-3.12.0-4
  ocaml-lablgl-1.04-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.20.51-2
  cygport-0.10.0-1
  flexdll-0.25-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.0-1
  make-3.81-2
  ocaml-findlib-1.2.6-1

Canonical website:
  http://ocamlsdl.sourceforge.net/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/ocamlsdl/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack ocaml-sdl-0.8.0-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./ocaml-sdl-0.8.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ocaml-sdl-0.8.0-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/ocaml-sdl-0.8.0-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Port Notes:

